					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">SuperFamicom.org is the only cart database I know of. Perhaps icarus in higan might help?<br /><br />For a ROM whose size is not a power of two, you'll want to split it at the largest power of 2 no larger than the ROM and then double up the remainder as big as the first. For example, you'd split a 10 Mbit ROM into 8 and 2 Mbit pieces and then quadruple the 2 Mbit part.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="https://pineight.com/nes/" class="postlink">Pin Eight</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/PinoBatch" class="postlink">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://github.com/pinobatch" class="postlink">GitHub</a> | <a href="https://patreon.com/pineight" class="postlink">Patreon</a></div>
